ess of the sampling of climatic niches by citizen science data. Variation in the p of SDMs for both types of data (as measured by the true skill statistic; TSS) was highly similar but SDMs from citizen science data had an overall lower performance. Nevertheless a few species achieved good predictions (TSS&gt;0.6) using these data. We conclude that species observations in citizen science projects can provide accurate predictions of species realized distributions, however, efforts should be made to identify the conditions under which these data are more likely to provide reliable representations of the species niches.", "access_right": "restricted", "creators": [{"name": "Tiago, Patr\u00edcia", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Pereira, Henrique M.", "affiliation": null}, {"name": "Capinha, C\u00e9sar", "affiliation": null}], "keywords": ["Chapter 6", "biodiversity", "environment assessment", "IPBES", "Alien Invasive Species Assessment AIS", "invasive species"], "related_identifiers": [{"identifier": "hash://md5/e0cae92e203cbf0aaed8d66cd3396ecd", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://sha256/f1c813126b3e787fa8842aa2f8af3c77a95cc9f420d971a26646276826696d71", "relation": "hasVersion", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "zotero://select/groups/2352922/items/4PQXI5E3", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://zotero.org/groups/2352922/items/4PQXI5E3", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "https://linker.bio/cut:hash://md5/05e65d42917641d1c37bf1a619bfc6bd!/b130968-135153", "relation": "isDerivedFrom", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "hash://md5/359bd494433933b868f85e88d3437f76", "relation": "isPartOf", "scheme": "url"}, {"identifier": "10.1016/j.baae.2017.04.001", "relation": "isVariantFormOf", "resource_type": "publication", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo.7430682", "relation": "isCitedBy", "resource_type": "publication-report", "scheme": "doi"}, {"identifier": "10.5281/zenodo